description: I am used to wearing a mask, it becomes a part of me. I notice that it is convenient for me to wear a mask not only because I comply with COVID-19 countermeasures, but also because I want to hide my emotions, stop being ashamed of my words, breathe less dirty air on streets filled with cars and dust. I imagine that I am getting better, because only my eyes are visible, in which what I am looking at is always reflected, I increasingly look defocused in order to capture beauty or because of the inability to focus on one thing.
